				<p><p>The question is a bit vague, but I would say that you at least need to spend ~$16 in a Bluetooth receiver. I have experience with roving networks modules, such as the <a href="http://www.rovingnetworks.com/products/RN_42" rel="nofollow">RN42</a>, which are easy to set up as wireless serial ports (you can talk to them via <a href="http://pyserial.sourceforge.net/" rel="nofollow">pyserial</a> or the like).</p>
</p><br>
